The evidence with the title '11 essential questions about crimea, answered | New Republic ' says Mar 7, 2014  ... Russia has always considered Crimea its property . It was part of Russia for the better part of two centuries until Nikita Krushchev gifted the land to what was then theUkrainian Soviet Socialist Republic in 1954 . When Ukraine declared independence from the USSR in 1991 , Crimea became part of Ukraine  ... 
